    <p>EX-DO­MES­TIC WORKER AC­QUIT­TED: A for­mer do­mes­tic helper has been cleared by the High Court of steal­ing more than $34,000 worth of items from Changi Air­port Group chair­man Liew Mun Leong and his fam­ily. ST Face­book users were glad that the less for­tu­nate could get le­gal help. Gita Sesh said: “Nice to know that the poor and vul­ner­a­ble are helped when they are falsely ac­cused. Well done to the le­gal sys­tem and the pro bono lawyer who de­fended her.”</p>
    <p>STUDY ON AIR­BORNE COVID-19 SPREAD: ST Face­book users were dis­turbed anew by a fresh study that some­one on a poorly ven­ti­lated Chi­nese bus in­fected nearly two dozen pas­sen­gers with the coro­n­avirus. Rob­bin Poh said: “Need to go back to 1980s bus with open win­dow, no air­con. Or spe­cial Hepa air fil­ter in air­con.”</p>


